                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>No. 391.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Porter</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Gurry</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1886-09-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 29, 1886</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Curry is informed that there is very urgent necessity that the commercial
                    agreement made with him should be promptly and satisfactorily enforced in Cuba;
                    that the authority granted by statute to the President to permit the continuance
                    to Spain of the special privileges which had been granted, rested solely on the
                    ground that these same privileges were to be accorded and continued to the
                    United States; that if the latter are interrupted from any cause whatsoever, the
                    President will be obliged to withdraw those accorded by the proclamation of
                    1884, and that there can be no delay, under the present condition of
                    circumstances, in this withdrawal.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
